%N A394378 Shortest sides x of primitive integer-sided triangles (x <= y <= z) with integer distance between circumcenter O and centroid G; ordered by increasing z, then y, then x.
%C A394378 The longest and middle sides are listed as A394376 and A394377, respectively. The corresponding distances OG are in A394379.
%e A394378 1 is a term because for the triangle (x, y, z) = (1, 1, 1) we have OG = 0.
%e A394378 5 is a term because for the triangle (x, y, z) = (5, 7, 8) we have OG = 1.
%e A394378 7 is a term because for the triangle (x, y, z) = (7, 8, 13) we have OG = 5.
